`Ad rejected the Messengers.{{88}}
|26|124|
Remember the time when their brother Hud said to them,{{89}} "Do you not fear?
|26|125|
I am a Messenger to you worthy of full trust:
|26|126|
so fear Allah and obey me.
|26|127|
I do not ask of you any reward for this duty, for my reward is with the Lord of the worlds.
|26|128|
What! you erect for mere pleasure, a monument on every high spot,{{90}}
|26|129|
and build huge castles as if you were immortal;{{91}}
|26|130|
and when you seize somebody, you seize him like a tyrant.{{92}}
|26|131|
So fear Allah and obey me. Fear .
|26|132|
Him Who has bestowed on you all that you know:
|26|133|
He gave you cattle and children
|26|134|
