|82|1|
When the heaven is split asunder,{{1}}
|82|2|
when the stars are scattered,
|82|3|
when the seas are made to burst forth,
|82|4|
and when graves are laid open,{{2}}
|82|5|
everyone shall know all his deeds, both the earlier and the later.{{3}}
|82|6|
O man! What has deceived you about your generous Lord
|82|7|
Who created you, shaped you, and made you well-proportioned,
|82|8|
and set you in whatever form He pleased?{{4}}
|82|9|
